There was both excitement and nervousness among new beginners and Grade 1 learners from Ladysmith and surrounding districts, as they began their schooling journey, on Wednesday 13 January.Most Grade 1 learners were very eager to start their first day at school, but others suddenly burst into tears when their parents left school. They felt uneasy being away from the comfort of their homes and the attention of their parents. They will now have to learn to adapt to school routine and begin a new chapter in their lifeChildren are resilient and quickly adapt to the change from home life to school routine.